# Your Spark job runs twice

- By default, **every action re-runs the whole lineage** from source.
- `.count()` then `.collect()` on the same RDD = computed **twice**.
- **`.cache()`** — materialize on first action, reuse after (RAM).
- **`.persist(level)`** — pick the policy: `MEMORY_ONLY`, `MEMORY_AND_DISK`, `DISK_ONLY`, `*_SER`, `*_2`.
- **`.unpersist()`** when done — a cache holds executor memory until released.
